1
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:27,120
You didn't die?

2
00:00:29,810 --> 00:00:30,850
I'm still alive.

3
00:00:31,730 --> 00:00:32,670
Thanks to you.

4
00:00:33,060 --> 00:00:35,550
♪ Time flies like a dream ♪

5
00:00:39,380 --> 00:00:43,050
♪ I remember every moonlight ♪

6
00:00:47,170 --> 00:00:48,470
Two grown men,

7
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:50,780
acting like children.

8
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,400
Mentor.

9
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:55,320
I just wanted to see if he was okay.

10
00:00:57,490 --> 00:00:58,640
I'm fully recovered.

11
00:00:58,640 --> 00:00:59,370
I'm fine now.

12
00:01:00,610 --> 00:01:03,090
♪ The memories overlap like a dream ♪

13
00:01:01,980 --> 00:01:03,520
The Zhang family's miraculous medicine

14
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:04,980
is really extraordinary.

15
00:01:06,420 --> 00:01:12,010
♪ What is lost and found again
runs deeper than farewell ♪

16
00:01:15,710 --> 00:01:17,039
Are you really fine now?

17
00:01:21,930 --> 00:01:24,150
You should worry about yourself.

18
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:57,350
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

19
00:02:57,780 --> 00:03:00,430
[Episode 16]

20
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:07,180
The headquarters is still the best.

21
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,300
If I got these injuries in Nanyang,

22
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:10,300
I'd be dead by now.

23
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,330
It hurts. Be gentle.

24
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:18,470
Shrimpie.

25
00:03:20,090 --> 00:03:22,950
The three of us
will live a good life here from now on.

26
00:03:25,620 --> 00:03:26,600
You should thank me and Zhang Haixia

27
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:30,329
for changing your dressings.
That's why you recovered so quickly.

28
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:32,680
You got like this just from doing a job.

29
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:33,910
So useless.

30
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:36,630
I'm not entirely useless, am I?

31
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,730
Didn't I bring him back?

32
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,530
What about his legs?

33
00:03:58,579 --> 00:03:59,770
Didn't Mentor say

34
00:04:00,970 --> 00:04:03,170
that this antidote cures all diseases?

35
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:06,430
That means there's still a chance

36
00:04:06,650 --> 00:04:08,060
for my legs to recover.

37
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,330
Really?

38
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,050
Are you kidding?

39
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:17,740
Really.

40
00:04:18,990 --> 00:04:20,620
The Zhang family's miraculous medicine

41
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:22,079
is absolutely effective.

42
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:24,160
He has an incomplete spinal injury,

43
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:26,290
meaning his spinal cord is damaged,

44
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:28,530
but some neural pathways remain.

45
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:29,720
In this situation,

46
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:32,140
the patient might retain some sensation

47
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:33,540
and motor function.

48
00:04:34,570 --> 00:04:35,840
And Zhang Hailou,

49
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:38,200
thanks to your dedication

50
00:04:38,850 --> 00:04:40,470
over the past three years,

51
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:42,300
caring for his legs

52
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,430
and helping him
with rehabilitation exercises,

53
00:04:44,430 --> 00:04:46,960
his muscles
haven't atrophied too severely.

54
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:48,610
The medicine from downstairs
in the Archives

55
00:04:48,610 --> 00:04:50,940
has already started to take effect on him.

56
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:53,090
He has a chance to stand up again.

57
00:05:07,410 --> 00:05:08,670
Did you bump your head?

58
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:11,600
No.

59
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:15,390
As soon as I came back and saw...

60
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:18,850
that Shrimpie is still alive,

61
00:05:19,950 --> 00:05:21,580
and his legs can recover,

62
00:05:23,150 --> 00:05:24,640
it just feels a bit too good

63
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,370
to be true.

64
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:32,520
Stop laughing.

65
00:05:45,860 --> 00:05:47,450
Isn't this the Zhang family's old mansion?

66
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:49,110
You're the daughter
of the Dong family now.

67
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:50,540
Why did you move back to the old mansion?

68
00:05:50,540 --> 00:05:51,750
The Dong family was bombed.

69
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:52,880
It's being rebuilt.

70
00:05:53,180 --> 00:05:54,640
So I bought this place back

71
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:56,480
in the name of the Dong family.

72
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:59,010
It feels good
to spend other people's money.

73
00:05:59,010 --> 00:06:00,390
You didn't expect this, did you?

74
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:01,650
After all these years,

75
00:06:01,810 --> 00:06:03,340
we can still come back here.

76
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,360
From now on, we'll be just like before,

77
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,890
living here together.

78
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,380
How wonderful would it be.

79
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,960
Finally, we're all back.

80
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:31,450
Let's go look around.

81
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:32,659
Let's go.

82
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:34,780
Shrimpie.

83
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,220
Mentor even restored this place?

84
00:07:49,810 --> 00:07:50,830
Mentor!

85
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:52,640
What is this?

86
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,560
I'm done playing.

87
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,280
Mentor, we're done playing!

88
00:08:12,810 --> 00:08:14,110
Mentor, come out.

89
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:15,560
We're done playing.

90
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:31,720
Mentor!

91
00:08:32,010 --> 00:08:33,470
You're tricking me again!

92
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:38,100
You two idiots!

93
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:41,169
You fell into such a simple trap!

94
00:08:41,940 --> 00:08:43,280
Stay hungry today.

95
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:45,390
I can't hold on anymore! Help!

96
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:46,910
Mentor!

97
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:52,190
I can't hold on, Mentor!

98
00:09:14,890 --> 00:09:15,860
Zhang Hailou.

99
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,130
You're a member of the Zhang family now.

100
00:09:18,130 --> 00:09:19,740
You need to act like a Zhang.

101
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:21,970
Starting tomorrow,

102
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:25,540
you will undergo
the Zhang family's training.

103
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:27,720
What training?

104
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,890
This.

105
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,250
When you can pull this brick out,

106
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:41,650
you'll have completed your first lesson.

107
00:09:42,010 --> 00:09:42,950
Take your time.

108
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,320
Are you kidding me?

109
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,290
Cut the crap.

110
00:09:49,050 --> 00:09:51,390
Zhang Haixia also needs to continue
his rehabilitation.

111
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:52,750
You two do your own things.

112
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:53,860
Don't bother each other.

113
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:55,550
We don't have many days to waste.

114
00:09:55,550 --> 00:09:58,170
There are still many things
to handle in the Archives.

115
00:09:58,170 --> 00:09:59,580
Are you even human?

116
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,250
Shouldn't we be reminiscing
about the past,

117
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:04,280
recalling the good times,

118
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,940
and feeling the moment
at a time like this?

119
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:07,360
Reminiscing about the past?

120
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,100
Alright.

121
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,600
Then tell me about all the

122
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:12,830
good deeds you did in Nanyang one by one.

123
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:14,820
Let's start...

124
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,510
with the Evil God Case.

125
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:21,360
Th-That's a long story.

126
00:10:22,220 --> 00:10:23,480
Why don't you go first?

127
00:10:31,050 --> 00:10:32,030
Mentor.

128
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:34,460
Well, it's been 10 years.

129
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:35,830
It's...

130
00:10:36,050 --> 00:10:37,180
It's all in the past.

131
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:38,240
Mentor, you...

132
00:10:39,630 --> 00:10:41,430
How come you haven't aged at all?

133
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:44,020
Share your skincare

134
00:10:44,050 --> 00:10:45,520
secrets with me, will you?

135
00:10:46,510 --> 00:10:47,220
Tell me.

136
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:52,190
I suddenly remembered
something very important.

137
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:52,980
Come with me.

138
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:01,270
[iKiwi Film Company]

139
00:11:07,550 --> 00:11:08,630
The important thing you mentioned

140
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:10,090
was just coming out to eat?

141
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:13,500
Me being hungry
is the most important thing in the world.

142
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,740
Why not eat at home?

143
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,220
It's Mid-Autumn Festival today.

144
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:18,480
Just listen to Mentor.

145
00:11:20,170 --> 00:11:23,800
[Jufang Restaurant]

146
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:26,430
Miss, gentlemen, your Siguo Soup,

147
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,670
pancakes,

148
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:31,430
sandworm jelly...

149
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:33,250
Shrimpie,

150
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:33,980
have a sausage first.

151
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:34,860
Stir-fried dried tofu,

152
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:36,270
pearl meatballs,

153
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:37,890
fresh fish dumplings,

154
00:11:38,220 --> 00:11:39,790
lovebirds fish rolls,

155
00:11:39,980 --> 00:11:41,510
and American crispy puffs.

156
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:42,960
All the dishes are here.

157
00:11:43,050 --> 00:11:43,980
Enjoy your meal.

158
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:05,920
Are you crying?

159
00:12:07,220 --> 00:12:08,550
Have you no conscience?

160
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,050
You didn't even cry for me,

161
00:12:10,050 --> 00:12:11,720
but now you're crying for some food?

162
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:12,980
You don't understand.

163
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:15,100
I've been craving this for 10 years.

164
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,090
Excuse me.

165
00:12:17,050 --> 00:12:17,720
Please bring us another round

166
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,670
of all these dishes later.

167
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:19,550
Okay.

168
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,010
Come on, try this.

169
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:22,980
Mentor,

170
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:24,820
can't the cooks in the Dong family

171
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:26,240
make these dishes?

172
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:29,890
Of course it's because
there's something good here.

173
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:30,510
Excuse me.

174
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:31,660
Coming!

175
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:33,460
Miss.

176
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,630
I heard you have the best

177
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:36,600
Green Spring wine in Xiacheng.

178
00:12:37,170 --> 00:12:39,050
I can tell you know your stuff.

179
00:12:39,130 --> 00:12:39,980
Green Spring

180
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:41,760
is our signature.

181
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:44,480
Many guests come here especially for it.

182
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:46,320
What vintage do you want?

183
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:47,930
The older, the better.

184
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:50,630
Then it depends on your luck today.

185
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,550
Look, this jar of

186
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:53,890
20-year-old wine

187
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:58,400
[Green Spring]

188
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:55,330
is our best.

189
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:57,360
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

190
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:00,050
Whoever wins the dice game

191
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:01,220
and takes the title of "Top Scholar"

192
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:03,790
gets this 20-year-old wine.

193
00:13:17,210 --> 00:13:20,050
Four red fours! Top Scholar!

194
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:18,340
[Four red fours] [Five of a kind with an ace]
[Top Scholar with two aces] [Five kings] [Six fours]

195
00:13:20,210 --> 00:13:21,180
Top Scholar!

196
00:13:21,390 --> 00:13:22,770
You have good luck, Miss.

197
00:13:22,770 --> 00:13:23,550
My turn!

198
00:13:40,390 --> 00:13:42,250
Five of a kind with an ace!

199
00:13:42,540 --> 00:13:44,070
Bigger than four red fours!

200
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,780
[Four red fours] [Five of a kind with an ace]
[Top Scholar with two aces] [Five kings] [Six fours]

201
00:13:59,390 --> 00:14:00,150
Five fours.

202
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:05,810
Five kings!

203
00:14:05,890 --> 00:14:08,150
The biggest Top Scholar so far!

204
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:11,480
The three of you
all made Top Scholar in a row.

205
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:14,350
We will definitely
have good luck next year!

206
00:14:14,670 --> 00:14:15,560
However,

207
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:18,050
[Green Spring]

208
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:18,750
we only have one jar of Green Spring.

209
00:14:18,940 --> 00:14:20,820
You three will have to share it.

210
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:22,050
It's fine. We are together.

211
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:22,720
Hold on.

212
00:14:23,390 --> 00:14:24,920
Since there's only one jar,

213
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:27,110
whoever gets the highest roll wins it.

214
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:28,820
You two brats.

215
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:30,200
When I started gambling,

216
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,050
your parents were still wearing diapers.

217
00:14:32,050 --> 00:14:32,710
Put it down.

218
00:14:33,670 --> 00:14:34,890
You old woman.

219
00:14:34,890 --> 00:14:36,270
We didn't spend all these years out there

220
00:14:36,270 --> 00:14:37,820
-making a living for nothing!
-What did you call me?

221
00:14:37,820 --> 00:14:39,100
Since there are three of us...

222
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:39,670
You...

223
00:14:40,050 --> 00:14:41,160
Let's play big.

224
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:43,170
Whoever rolls the lowest

225
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:44,010
pays for everyone!

226
00:14:44,010 --> 00:14:44,750
-Great!
-Really?

227
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:45,250
Bravo!

228
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:45,830
Really?

229
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:47,030
Great!

230
00:14:47,940 --> 00:14:48,510
Awesome!

231
00:14:48,510 --> 00:14:48,970
Great!

232
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:53,550
This big?

233
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:56,100
Do you have a plan?

234
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:58,530
You go first.

235
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:06,390
I learned all my cheating tricks
from Mentor.

236
00:15:06,390 --> 00:15:07,390
What should we do?

237
00:15:08,230 --> 00:15:11,070
Are you stupid?
I also learned them from her.

238
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:13,550
Aren't you full of tricks?

239
00:15:13,550 --> 00:15:14,680
Think of something.

240
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:19,610
Six fours!

241
00:15:19,670 --> 00:15:21,500
The biggest Top Scholar so far!

242
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:23,350
Awesome!

243
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:25,390
Do you have money on you?

244
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:26,320
No.

245
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,320
What should we do?

246
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,740
We're on the same team.

247
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,610
He'll pay if we lose.

248
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:32,420
You do it.

249
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:56,170
Another one!

250
00:16:00,050 --> 00:16:00,790
Again?

251
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:01,540
Again?

252
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:02,600
Again!

253
00:16:09,420 --> 00:16:10,430
Again?

254
00:16:11,390 --> 00:16:12,530
Still winning?

255
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:13,710
Awesome. Awesome.

256
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:16,680
A win!

257
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:17,900
A win again!

258
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,850
A win! A win!

259
00:16:20,870 --> 00:16:22,440
A win!

260
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:23,870
A win! A win!

261
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:25,650
A win! A win!

262
00:16:25,670 --> 00:16:27,370
A win! A win!

263
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:29,430
A win! A win!

264
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:33,870
A win! A win!

265
00:16:34,050 --> 00:16:37,320
A win! A win!

266
00:16:37,340 --> 00:16:41,320
A win! A win!

267
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:43,200
Bravo!

268
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:45,090
Top Scholar with two aces!

269
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:46,840
Shrimpie, we won!

270
00:16:47,050 --> 00:16:47,830
We won!

271
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:48,720
Shrimpie!

272
00:16:52,050 --> 00:16:53,360
Congratulations, Top Scholars.

273
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,820
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

274
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:55,820
Here is a photographer.

275
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:57,200
He can take a picture of you

276
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,060
to record this wonderful moment.

277
00:16:59,940 --> 00:17:00,650
Mentor,

278
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,870
I want to take it standing up.

279
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,859
Shrimpie, let me help you.

280
00:17:26,810 --> 00:17:28,460
Come on, bottoms up.

281
00:17:40,010 --> 00:17:41,540
It's rare to have good wine.

282
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,260
I want some spicy fish.

283
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,280
Haixia, make it for me tomorrow.

284
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:47,730
Mentor.

285
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:51,200
Spicy fish—if he makes it tomorrow,

286
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:52,900
you won't get to eat it.

287
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:54,400
You'll have to wait a few days.

288
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,590
Talking back again!

289
00:17:55,610 --> 00:17:57,550
You've been talking back to me
since childhood!

290
00:17:57,550 --> 00:17:59,020
I mean... let's...

291
00:17:59,310 --> 00:18:00,510
Let's talk business.

292
00:18:01,050 --> 00:18:01,850
The Archives.

293
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:09,440
The Residence was attacked,
the Ship King was killed,

294
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:11,440
and the Archives were almost made public.

295
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:14,240
There's been such a huge disturbance
in Xiacheng.

296
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:16,480
I need time to deal with the aftermath.

297
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,780
I need to go out for a few days.

298
00:18:19,310 --> 00:18:20,900
You two can take the opportunity

299
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:21,810
to rest.

300
00:18:22,050 --> 00:18:23,810
Rest? Does something this good
really exist?

301
00:18:23,810 --> 00:18:25,200
Let's go fishing tomorrow.

302
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:27,000
We haven't fished in a long time.

303
00:18:27,050 --> 00:18:28,580
And when Mentor comes back,

304
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:29,850
we can have spicy fish.

305
00:18:29,850 --> 00:18:31,850
Didn't you use to hate me fishing
the most?

306
00:18:31,850 --> 00:18:33,440
Every time we came out fishing,
you said...

307
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:34,310
you said I cheated.

308
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:35,010
This time,

309
00:18:35,010 --> 00:18:36,400
you prepare good bait for me,

310
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:37,660
and I'll let you get
a three-fish head start. Okay?

311
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:39,400
Why? Why?

312
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:46,720
[iKiwi Film Company]

313
00:18:48,850 --> 00:18:49,670
Shrimpie.

314
00:18:50,770 --> 00:18:51,740
So nice.

315
00:18:55,730 --> 00:18:56,480
Look at that!

316
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:57,440
Look!

317
00:18:57,460 --> 00:18:58,200
It started!

318
00:18:58,220 --> 00:18:59,040
Over there!

319
00:18:58,790 --> 00:19:03,070
[iKiwi Film Company]

320
00:19:06,350 --> 00:19:12,150
♪ The past fades into traces on the page ♪

321
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:19,150
♪ A silent breeze
brushes past that lingering warmth ♪

322
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:16,840
[iKiwi Film Company]

323
00:19:20,540 --> 00:19:26,410
♪ In this fleeting world,
I long for a moment of vivid life ♪

324
00:19:20,810 --> 00:19:21,810
So beautiful.

325
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:32,130
♪ I may have a chance to open a door ♪

326
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:40,100
♪ Where love and wish
meet in a fleeting moment ♪

327
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:47,050
♪ There's no need to ask questions
in the maze ♪

328
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:43,860
Shrimpie,

329
00:19:44,270 --> 00:19:45,610
look at the green one.

330
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:50,030
♪ The world's bustle ♪

331
00:19:50,610 --> 00:19:55,520
♪ Can briefly warm
those under a shared roof ♪

332
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:59,780
[iKiwi Film Company]

333
00:19:56,600 --> 00:20:02,290
♪ And the story has come to an end ♪

334
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:11,080
[Xiacheng News]

335
00:20:12,170 --> 00:20:17,710
[Crossword Puzzle]

336
00:20:23,090 --> 00:20:23,590
Come on.

337
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:25,240
Try to move.

338
00:20:26,010 --> 00:20:26,470
Come on.

339
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:31,490
Push.

340
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:32,010
Yes.

341
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:35,400
Push.

342
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:41,980
Good.

343
00:20:42,270 --> 00:20:42,740
Good!

344
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:44,600
Take a rest.

345
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:48,870
Let's stop here for today.

346
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:50,980
Doctor.

347
00:20:51,590 --> 00:20:52,980
How much longer will it take

348
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:54,310
before I can try to walk?

349
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:56,640
You're making fast progress.

350
00:20:57,850 --> 00:20:58,910
Miss Dong told me

351
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,400
not to let you rush things.

352
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,400
Get plenty of rest

353
00:21:01,590 --> 00:21:03,050
so you can recover better.

354
00:21:03,620 --> 00:21:04,350
I'm leaving.

355
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:26,850
Let's go fishing tomorrow.

356
00:21:26,850 --> 00:21:28,240
We haven't fished in a long time.

357
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:29,740
And when Mentor comes back,

358
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:31,080
we can have spicy fish.

359
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:33,500
It's raining.

360
00:21:35,510 --> 00:21:37,110
Will the rain stop tomorrow?

361
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:49,190
This terrible weather! I...

362
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,160
My good bait is completely wasted.

363
00:21:56,550 --> 00:21:58,680
It wasn't easy to get this Shilixiang.

364
00:21:58,770 --> 00:22:00,630
I was planning to catch a big fish.

365
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:02,370
The weather is bad.

366
00:22:02,850 --> 00:22:04,200
There's nothing we can do.

367
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,190
I don't think so.

368
00:22:05,510 --> 00:22:06,770
Maybe, with this weather,

369
00:22:06,770 --> 00:22:08,370
the rain will stop in a while.

370
00:22:09,010 --> 00:22:10,070
Let me feel it.

371
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,100
Young Masters!

372
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:17,440
Are you going out?

373
00:22:17,980 --> 00:22:18,530
There...

374
00:22:18,810 --> 00:22:20,050
We've had a typhoon these past few days,

375
00:22:20,050 --> 00:22:21,270
and it'll probably last a few more days.

376
00:22:21,270 --> 00:22:22,670
It's better not to go out.

377
00:22:24,050 --> 00:22:25,980
-It's all wet.
-This weather is awful.

378
00:22:25,980 --> 00:22:27,900
Could it be the heavenly ghost
making trouble in Xiacheng?

379
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:29,810
I heard that
when the heavenly ghost appears,

380
00:22:29,810 --> 00:22:31,610
bad things will happen.

381
00:22:31,660 --> 00:22:32,510
Really?

382
00:22:37,660 --> 00:22:38,350
What year is this?

383
00:22:38,350 --> 00:22:40,280
They still believe this nonsense?

384
00:22:41,980 --> 00:22:42,610
Shrimpie,

385
00:22:43,770 --> 00:22:45,170
